column18:
Sorry for some bad photos in between this series of sightings.

I went for a day over to dive at Morro Jable.

I tried to map as many species as possible.

Surprisingly for me, I was overwhelmed with a lot of life.

For a month, I moved to Playa Honda.
I wanted to explore the waters in front a bit by snorkeling.
A very shallow area.
I think I didn't choose the best day.
Lots of wind and waves.

Together with @susannespider we went to 2 new dive sites.
I tried to map the species that can be found there.
Thanks to Piero Quarone Sport Sette Diving Andora (SV)
